        "Description": {
            "val": "Funding provides technical subject matter expertise, infrastructure and networks for the Persistent Cyber Training Environment (PCTE), supporting top secret and unclassified instance capability across the Department of Defense (DOD).  The program will provide a combination of loosely affiliated or independent virtual environments with varied capabilities that are scalable and extensible (the systemic measure to extend the ability of a system and the level of effort required to implement the extension through the addition of new functionality or through modification of existing functionality). Multiple DOD Component cyber ranges are expanding in varying stages of capability and capacity, and require a joint or standard approach for consistency and applicability.  PCTE will inform Cyber Range architecture to allow a mutually extensible network of capability at multiple organizational levels. The Cyber Mission Forces Persistent Training Environment Capability Based Assessment (CBA) identified requirements in PCTE Event Planning, Event Assessment, and Connectivity."
        },
        "Justification": {
            "val": "FY18 base procurement in the amount of $4.000 million supports the identification and resolution of gaps in connectivity across the Cyber Service component ranges.  Site surveys will analyze the compatibility of cyber ranges and cyber mission forces\u2019 training sites.  The identified shortfalls will be prioritized and satisfied with the available procurement funding.  Improved connectivity will include the procurement of transport, compute capability along with any associated operating systems.  The connectivity hardware and Operating System (OS) will provide a cloud-like environment which allows the Persistent Cyber Training Environment (PCTE) to utilize available compute, storage, and application resources across all the cyber ranges."
        },
